<br>
1. The wrong mix of people... i.e too much melee and not enough casters<br>
 (ya can't just beat the lizard down)<br>
<br>
2. No experienced leadership<br>
(I wasn't about to lead a horde of people to their deaths-better to have somebody that has done it successfully a few times lead a pickup. In my recruitment I discovered that there were plenty of people willing to go but no one willing to lead and those that have successfully downed VS before absolutely refused to assit - I guess VS is a &quot;members only&quot; type of mob.) <br>
<br>
<br>
When I was recruiting for a VS Pick up it was obvious that there was big excitement for people to join up- but what was needed was a sort of shopping list of people required to down VS.<br>
<br>
In other words we will need somebody who has successfully downed VS to post the count and class of people they had that did it.<br>
<br>
Also keep in mind that with pick-up raids there are always more people needed just because of inexperience- so any shopping list of needed people should be almost doubled in pick up situations.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp<br>
-Dunkamar<br>
<br>
p.s. VS is on rotation as a courtesy between guilds- there is nothing preventing ambitious people from starting a pickup raid. I know this has sparked much debate in the past but fact is no one owns or polices mobs- this does not create chaos- Honestly, how many pick up raids do you think could 1- be successful and 2- if they were how would this be a bad thing?<br>
<br>
More people getting to play uber mobs= more fun for all.<br>
